videoDescription: ear-sight's 2nd party â› Gone Fishin' tickets â› https://bit.ly/32wBf2V 23.11 â  23 Uhr â  Burg Schnabel FB Event â¡ï¸ https://bit.ly/2JZGtgO RA â¡ï¸ https://bit.ly/2WRPXjA ear-sight are back to champion the celebrated and lesser-known producers of lofi hip hop and house music across Europe, with their second Gone Fishin' party at cosy Kreuzberg venue Burg Schnabel this November. Another sickeningly talent-ridden line up to keep us dancing and/or chin stroking all night, with a few of the artists playing both the disco/house and hip hop room with their own unreleased productions/selections - Ever wondered what sort of house digitalluc might make, if he made house for example? Well, he does, and you need not wonder any more ;) Kicking the night off in the house/disco room is cut master DJ Educut, whoâ€™s scratching youâ€™ve likely heard on a Figub BrazleviÄ record or two, playing us some lofi house. Over from Rotterdam, Chill Hop chief and veteran EU beats producer Philanthrope will also be throwing down some of his uptempo work, as will Berlin/Paris beat dons S. Fidelity and Bluestaeb - Weâ€™re also lucky to have Fibug Brazlevic joining us in the hip hop room; protect ur neck or you might get whiplash off this setâ€¦ ! Finally, seeing us through to 8.30am, expect tripped-out jazzy house from Blaqnumberâ€™s/Get Togetherâ€™s Donnie Moustaki and some serious smooth disco/house from Razor n Tapeâ€™s/Get Togetherâ€™s Cody Currie. Kick back with a cold one, a jazz-cigarette and some world-class music. Gone Fishinâ€™ Bebe

videoTitle: East-West Sessions #003 w/ MOONTROOP & COMETEERS Teaser
videoDescription: East-West Session #003 "From musicians for musicians" The East-West sessions try to bring together various musicians from different genres, disciplines and styles into one big live jam session. Most of the artists involved know each other from their respective individual projects but the East-West Sessions strive to mix them all together on one stage, away from their bedroom studios and laptops. The vibe is organic and loose with the occupation of the stage and the instruments constantly changing and artists inviting each other onto the stage and improvising away. The jam takes place at Panke, an inspiring location in the heart of Berlin's vibrant Wedding district - the venue buzzes with creativity, hosting various party concepts, workshops and exhibitions throughout the year. videoTitle: DLTLLY // Interview with ONRA (Producer)
videoDescription: WEBSITEâ–ºhttp://bit.ly/1gbppjC TWITTERâ–ºhttp://bit.ly/1f27E1W FBâ–ºhttp://on.fb.me/19h5qtg SHOPâ–ºhttp://bit.ly/1iohDCD APPLY/BEWERBENâ–ºDontLetTheLabelLabelYouTV@gmail.com We met up for an interview with Onra a couple of months back before his show in Berlin. Onra is a ground-breaking producer who lives in Paris and has released 6 albums since starting to make music in 2006. His debut album, Chinoiseries came into being after his first trip to Vietnam from which he brought back over 30 Chinese and Vietnamese records from the 60's and 70's. Chinoiseries is a ground-breaking album compiled of 32 tracks that blend Hip-Hop and Vietnamese Pop Music influences. Onra released Chinoiseries Part II in 2011 which picks up where Part I left of. Regardless of the many genres Onra has dabbled with since, his approach to his production remains that of a Hip Hop producer. Sampling records with an MPC. Originally from Spain but currently based in Berlin Kid Simius has made a real name for himself within the electronic music scene in Germany.
